args:
Jupiter uses both evidence and reason to push
back against the prosecution's arguments.
But just when things are going well, someone
offers up false testimony, leaving him in a bind.
The Day of the Trial\nLittleton Courthouse Waiting Room

Hey there, Princey! I got a treat for you!
You get to come to the courtroom too!
Oh, but the lawyer? He's locked up tight.
'Cause that's what you all agreed to, right?

Don't pretend to be helping, you rascals!
I already got permission for a temporary
release AND for him to sit in on the
trial, so you shouldn't even be here.
Now stay out of my way and stop trying\nto confuse the issue!
Thanks, Jupiter. It's no surprise those\nimperials are trying every dirty trick\nin the book to stop us.
Yeah, but I didn't know they'd be THIS into\nit. How much is that bloated dolt of a\nprosecutor paying them, anyway?

An awful lot, I'd imagine. The Empire may
be in bad shape these days, but using
another nation's soldiers as personal
lackeys can't be cheap.
But all that nonsense ends today.\nNow let's win this trial!
I'm surprised how calm the courtroom is,\ngiven how many soldiers we saw hanging\naround town.

My great grandfather built this into an
honorable place, which makes it all the
worse that it's now being used for such
underhanded shenanigans!
Hear ye, hear ye! Court is now in session!\nThe prosecution will now present\ntheir opening statement.

Thank you, Your Honor... Hear me well,
you ignorant masses and defendants!
I will now present to you a perfect picture
of absolute guilt!

Three days ago, the defendant you see
before you took a back road in the
shopping district and plunged a knife
into the back of an innocent victim!

The prosecution will now call to the stand
an eyewitness to this crime. Sir, please
tell us your name and exactly what you
saw on that heinous day.
My name is Gassbag, and I was the first\nto witness this most dastardly deed!

That day, I happened to be wandering near
the scene of the crime when I heard a
woman scream! Oh, it was a terrible
sound, so it was. TEEEEEERRIBLE!

Sadly, by the time I got there, the victim
was already dead—and I clearly saw that
the knife sticking out of his back had the
defendant's family crest upon it!

There was nobody else in that entire
alley, so I can say without a shadow
of a doubt that the defendant is guilty!
GUILTY! GUILTY AS SIN!
Thank you, sir. Does the defendant have\nanything to ask this witness? Are there\nany issues you have with his testimony?
Only the fact he's lying through his teeth!\nI mean, the victim was already dead by\nthe time I got there for heck's sake!

Naturally, we have many issues with the
prosecution's claims. Thankfully, I have
something that may shed light on the
contradictions in our witness's testimony.

Let's take it back to the beginning, yes?
In truth, the murder weapon had actually
been stolen from the defendant's house
some time before the crime.

As evidence, we present an investigative
report drawn up by the Templars based on the
testimony of the secondhand shopkeeper who
acquired the item.
This same dealer also gave us a detailed\ndescription of the person who bought the\nknife in question.

He was ＂a young man with brown hair,
brown eyes, a slouch, and a loud voice.＂
And my stars, but that is a PERFECT
description of our witness here today!
Order! Order! That is a very inflammatory\nstatement, Mr. Defense Attorney.\nWhat exactly do you mean by it?

Only this, Your Honor: At the time of the
crime, the person who was in possession
of the murder weapon was not my client,
but the witness himself!

And as Mr. Gassbag so kindly admitted,
the only people at the scene of the crime
were my client and himself, which means
we can only draw one conclusion...
Gassbag is the murderer, and my client\nhas been set up!
Did you see Gassbag's reaction just now?\nJupiter's really on to something here!
Don't be absurd! This is nothing more than\nan absolute fantasy brought on by the\ngreatest of all fools.

Is there wax in your ears, my dear?
This whole absurd allegation is based on
nothing more than the testimony of a
single shopkeeper.
This is a baseless accusation founded on\nthe flimsiest of personal descriptions, and\nit absolutely will not stand.
Yeah, what he said! How can we even trust\nthe memory of some old coot anyway?!
Hmm... I don't recall saying that the\nshopkeep in question was an old man.
Now how in Alberia could you possibly\nhave known that little factoid?

Aha ha ha! You know, I figured you were
the kind of loose-lipped person who would
incriminate himself, which is exactly why
I left that little detail out.
Wait, so you were deliberately trying to\nget under the witness's skin in order to\nmake him slip up?
That's so Jupiter. He even managed to\ntake into consideration what arguments\nthe prosecution might make!
At this rate, we'll be found innocent\nin no time!
It seems the defense has finished.\nProsecution, would you like to\npresent any further evidence?
I would, Your Honor. The prosecution\ncalls a new witness to the stand!
Muh name's Barr Gayne, and I run that\nthere secondhand store where the murder\nweapon was sold, a'yup.
'Fraid I gotta give muh apologies\nto the Templars, so I does.
Told 'em all 'bout the customer what\ncame in to buy that knife, but them I\nrealize I plumb misremembered it all!

I was so startled when I saw them there
Templars, I just blurted out whatever came
into muh fool head. Please don't pay it
no nevermind, Yer Honorableness.
Truth is, I sold that knife to a woman.\nLooked right like that one there,\nso she did. A'yup.

You all seem very confused over there,
so permit me to explain. The defense's
absurd theory that poor Mr. Gassbag was
somehow at fault has fallen apart.

With this new testimony, we can now say
with absolute certainty that the actual
culprit is the defendant! Isn't that right,
dear girl?!
You have GOT to be KIDDING ME!
I can't believe this! Why the heck did that\nold fart suddenly change his tune?!
That's perjury if I've ever heard it.\nI'm guessing the prosecutor went behind\nour backs and paid that shopkeep off.

Last night, most likely. I assume he saw
how my brilliant defense would shred his
case like a catapult through a tissue and
came up with a countermeasure.
Once he saw our hand, he deployed his\nlittle ace in the hole. Oh, but he's a\nsneaky snake, make no mistake!
Defense, do you have a rebuttal\nfor the prosecution's argument?
We sure do: He's a big fat lying liar\nwho LIES ALL THE TIME!
Look, there's no choice here, guys:\nWe have to find a way to prove the truth.
Agreed, but it won't be easy to prove\nperjury in so little time.

That shopkeep was the only one who saw
the purchaser of the knife, so if he sticks
to this cockamamie story, there isn't a
whole lot we can do.
YOU ARE THE WORST LAWYER EVER!
Augh! Stop shaking my collar like that!\nGood heavens! Your Honor, please!\nA quick recess, Your Honor?!
The defendant is clearly not in the right\nstate of mind to continue the trial!
Stalling for time, are we? Ha!\nThe last refuge of the damned.
The court will now take a brief recess.\nWhen we return, we will make our final\njudgment on the defendant!
